What problem do they solve by only permitting code rollouts twice a day?
They permitted code twice a day in order to commit defect number so it won’t affect the performance problem.


Why are they afraid of the auditors?
Under the payment card rule, they are not allowed to store or transmit anything on track 2. This is a cardholder data breach and it’s a big fine if the auditor fine out.


What is a NOC?  (It’s mentioned in the book and we’ve talked about it in class, but you may have to google it)
NOC is Network Operation Center. This center is the war room for the IT department.


Why do Bill and Chris decide to meet once a week?
They meet once a week to figure how to get the company to not outsource the IT.
